raw_meta_yaml:
context:
  name: rust-sasa-python
  version: "0.7.2"

package:
  name: ${{ name }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/rust_sasa_python-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4228ce70b462c1d9c42b87557837db011812e14c0134d5a1265df8b304b0c2c8

build:
  script: |
    cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output THIRDPARTY.yml
    ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation
  number: 0

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ compiler("c") }}
    - ${{ stdlib("c") }}
    - ${{ compiler("rust") }}
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - crossenv
        - maturin >=1.5,<2.0
        - python
  host:
    - python
    - maturin >=1.5,<2.0
    - pip
  run:
    - python

tests:
  - python:
      pip_check: true
      imports:
        - rust_sasa_python
      python_version: ${{ python }}

about:
  homepage: "https://pypi.org/project/rust-sasa-python"
  summary: "rust-sasa-python is a Python library for computing Solvent Accessible Surface Area (SASA/ASA) values for proteins."
  description: |
    A high-performance Python library for computing SASA (Solvent Accessible Surface Area) using Rust as the backend. 
    This library provides a clean, Pythonic interface to the fast RustSASA calculation engine.
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE.md
    - THIRDPARTY.yml
  repository: https://github.com/maxall41/rust-sasa-python
  documentation: https://github.com/maxall41/rust-sasa-python/blob/main/DOCS.md

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - eunos-1128
    - maxall41
